1024
00:57:24,567 --> 00:57:27,500
"We will never forget your
kindness" and

1025
00:57:27,500 --> 00:57:29,500
"God bless America."

1026
00:57:30,834 --> 00:57:33,867
We do these things because
they help promote

1027
00:57:33,867 --> 00:57:38,333
our long-term security, and we
do them because we believe

1028
00:57:38,333 --> 00:57:41,500
in the inherent dignity
and equality of every

1029
00:57:41,500 --> 00:57:45,734
human being, regardless of
race or religion,

1030
00:57:45,734 --> 00:57:47,500
creed or sexual orientation.

1031
00:57:47,500 --> 00:57:51,100
And next week, the world
will see one expression

1032
00:57:51,100 --> 00:57:54,066
of that commitment -- when
Team USA marches the red,

1033
00:57:54,066 --> 00:57:55,800
white, and blue into
the Olympic Stadium,

1034
00:57:55,800 --> 00:57:59,300
and brings home the gold.

1035
00:57:59,300 --> 00:58:05,266
[Applause]

1036
00:58:05,266 --> 00:58:07,233
Audience: USA!

1037
00:58:07,233 --> 00:58:09,200
USA!

1038
00:58:09,200 --> 00:58:17,266
USA!

1039
00:58:17,266 --> 00:58:20,467
The President: My fellow
Americans, no other

1040
00:58:20,467 --> 00:58:24,400
country in the world
does what we do.

1041
00:58:24,400 --> 00:58:26,667
On every issue, the world
turns

1042
00:58:26,667 --> 00:58:30,600
to us, not simply because of the
size of our economy

1043
00:58:30,600 --> 00:58:34,266
or our military might, but
because of the ideals we stand

1044
00:58:34,266 --> 00:58:41,166
for and the burdens we bear
to advance them.

1045
00:58:41,166 --> 00:58:42,667
No one knows this better
than those

1046
00:58:42,667 --> 00:58:43,633
who serve in uniform.

1047
00:58:45,667 --> 00:58:48,734
As this time of war
draws to a close,

1048
00:58:48,734 --> 00:58:51,734
a new generation of heroes
returns to civilian life.

1049
00:58:54,266 --> 00:58:56,200
We'll keep slashing that
backlog

1050
00:58:56,200 --> 00:58:58,400
so our veterans receive the
benefits they've earned,

1051
00:58:58,400 --> 00:59:01,367
and our wounded warriors receive
the health care --

1052
00:59:01,367 --> 00:59:03,300
including the mental
health care

1053
00:59:03,300 --> 00:59:05,467
-- that they need.

1054
00:59:05,467 --> 00:59:22,200
[Applause]

1055
00:59:22,200 --> 00:59:23,200
We'll keep
working to help

1056
00:59:23,200 --> 00:59:25,300
all our veterans translate their
skills

1057
00:59:25,300 --> 00:59:27,333
and leadership into jobs here at home.

1058
00:59:27,333 --> 00:59:31,266
And we will all continue
to join forces

1059
00:59:31,266 --> 00:59:34,300
to honor and support our
remarkable military families.

1060
00:59:34,300 --> 00:59:39,967
Let me tell you about one
of those families

1061
00:59:39,967 --> 00:59:42,633
I've come to know.

1062
00:59:42,633 --> 00:59:49,033
I first met Cory Remsburg,
a proud Army Ranger,

1063
00:59:49,033 --> 00:59:54,367
at Omaha Beach on the 65th
anniversary of D-Day.

1064
00:59:54,367 --> 00:59:56,000
Along with some of his
fellow Rangers,

1065
00:59:56,000 --> 00:59:59,300
he walked me through the program
and the ceremony.

1066
00:59:59,300 --> 01:00:01,033
He was a strong,
impressive young man,

1067
01:00:01,033 --> 01:00:03,333
had an easy manner, he
was sharp as a tack.

1068
01:00:03,333 --> 01:00:06,367
And we joked around and
took pictures,

1069
01:00:06,367 --> 01:00:07,867
and I told him to stay in touch.

1070
01:00:10,200 --> 01:00:14,900
A few months later, on his
tenth deployment,

1071
01:00:14,900 --> 01:00:18,066
Cory was nearly killed by a
massive roadside

1072
01:00:18,066 --> 01:00:20,066
bomb in Afghanistan.

1073
01:00:21,633 --> 01:00:23,433
His comrades found him
in a canal,

1074
01:00:23,433 --> 01:00:27,533
face down, underwater, shrapnel
in his brain.

1075
01:00:29,900 --> 01:00:32,033
For months, he
lay in a coma.

1076
01:00:32,033 --> 01:00:35,767
And the next time I met
him, in the hospital,

1077
01:00:35,767 --> 01:00:39,667
he couldn't speak,
could barely move.

1078
01:00:41,900 --> 01:00:44,533
Over the years, he's
endured dozens

1079
01:00:44,533 --> 01:00:48,266
of surgeries and procedures,
hours

1080
01:00:48,266 --> 01:00:49,767
of grueling rehab every day.

1081
01:00:52,100 --> 01:00:55,233
Even now, Cory is still
blind in one eye,

1082
01:00:55,233 --> 01:00:58,667
still struggles on
his left side.

1083
01:00:58,667 --> 01:01:03,200
But slowly, steadily, with
the support of caregivers

1084
01:01:03,200 --> 01:01:07,233
like his dad, Craig, and
the community around him,

1085
01:01:07,233 --> 01:01:08,600
Cory has grown stronger.

1086
01:01:08,600 --> 01:01:13,533
And, day by day, he's
learned to speak again

1087
01:01:13,533 --> 01:01:16,100
and stand again
and walk again.

1088
01:01:16,100 --> 01:01:19,266
And he's working toward
the day when

1089
01:01:19,266 --> 01:01:21,266
he can serve his country again.

1090
01:01:24,066 --> 01:01:26,734
"My recovery has not
been easy," he says.

1091
01:01:28,934 --> 01:01:32,467
"Nothing in life that's
worth anything is easy."

1092
01:01:35,700 --> 01:01:37,667
Cory is here tonight.

1093
01:01:37,667 --> 01:01:40,567
And like the Army he
loves, like the America

1094
01:01:40,567 --> 01:01:45,233
he serves, Sergeant First
Class Cory Remsburg never

1095
01:01:45,233 --> 01:01:46,767
gives up, and he
does not quit.

1096
01:01:46,767 --> 01:03:31,300
[Applause]

1097
01:03:31,300 --> 01:03:34,200
My fellow Americans, men
and women like Cory

1098
01:03:34,200 --> 01:03:39,133
remind us that America has
never come easy.

1099
01:03:41,433 --> 01:03:44,066
Our freedom, our
democracy,

1100
01:03:44,066 --> 01:03:46,066
has never been easy.

1101
01:03:47,300 --> 01:03:51,433
Sometimes we stumble,
we make mistakes;

1102
01:03:51,433 --> 01:03:53,433
we get frustrated or discouraged.

1103
01:03:55,433 --> 01:03:59,033
But for more than 200
years, we have put those

1104
01:03:59,033 --> 01:04:03,000
things aside and placed
our collective shoulder

1105
01:04:03,000 --> 01:04:06,533
to the wheel of progress --
to create and build

1106
01:04:06,533 --> 01:04:10,767
and expand the possibilities
of individual achievement;

1107
01:04:10,767 --> 01:04:13,100
to free other nations
from tyranny and fear;

1108
01:04:15,200 --> 01:04:19,633
to promote justice, and
fairness, and equality

1109
01:04:19,633 --> 01:04:22,166
under the law so that the
words set to paper

1110
01:04:22,166 --> 01:04:25,567
by our founders are made real
for every citizen.

1111
01:04:29,033 --> 01:04:31,800
The America we want for
our kids --

1112
01:04:31,800 --> 01:04:35,066
a rising America where honest
work is plentiful

1113
01:04:35,066 --> 01:04:39,200
and communities are strong;
where prosperity is widely

1114
01:04:39,200 --> 01:04:42,166
shared and opportunity for
all lets

1115
01:04:42,166 --> 01:04:45,367
us go as far as our dreams and
toil will take us --

1116
01:04:45,367 --> 01:04:46,367
none of it is easy.

1117
01:04:46,367 --> 01:04:53,367
But if we work together --
if we summon what

1118
01:04:53,367 --> 01:04:56,500
is best in us, the way Cory
summoned what is best

1119
01:04:56,500 --> 01:04:59,734
in him, with our feet planted
firmly in today

1120
01:04:59,734 --> 01:05:02,100
but our eyes cast toward
tomorrow --

1121
01:05:02,100 --> 01:05:04,333
I know it is within our reach.

1122
01:05:06,333 --> 01:05:07,467
Believe it.

1123
01:05:08,633 --> 01:05:09,900
God bless you, and God
bless

1124
01:05:09,900 --> 01:05:10,700
the United States of America.

1125
01:05:10,700 --> 01:05:17,166
[Applause]

